0.1 percent in January, according to the  Teranet-National Bank 
Composite House  Price Index .  Halifax,  Nova Scotia , led the increase with a 0.7 percent
gain, according to a report today by National Bank Financial.  Prices were 6.5 percent higher in January than a year
